    <p class="text-gray-700">If you enjoy Pinot Noir's light body and bright fruit, consider Gamay from Beaujolais, which offers similar drinkability at often lower prices. Sangiovese from Italy provides comparable acidity and food-friendliness, while Loire Valley Cabernet Franc offers elegant herbaceous notes. For those seeking more complexity, look for Côtes du Rhône or Spanish Tempranillo, which can deliver greater depth in the same price range.</p>
